cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DB, cs.SE, cs.CL 

The paper discusses reasoning with ontologies, which is a core field of research in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). It also mentions the use of highly optimized algorithms, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG). The investigation of particular ontological features and their correlation with reasoner performance falls under the category of database systems (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the empirical perspective of understanding reasoner behavior, which is a topic in software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper proposes a set of ontology features that can be used as indicators of ontology hardness level, which is a topic in natural language processing (cs.CL).
